form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: MAR Gong Doo Question 8 continued, Screened by NARA, 9/18/2023

full_text: Screened by NARA, 9/18/2023 MAR Gong Doo Question 8 continued Lee Shirt Pressing Co. (apprentice) Bronx, N.Y. June 1957 to Oct. 1957 M & M Shirt Laundry Inc. 1323 61st St., Brooklyn, N.Y. Oct. 1957 to date of accident Hospitalized. Beginning Dec. 25, 1957 to Oct. 8, 1958. Hit by automobile. M & M Shirt Pressing Laundry Inc. 1323 61st St., Brooklyn, N.Y. about Dec. 1959 to May 1960 Kang Wal Shirt Pressing Laundry Inc. 79 3rd St., Brooklyn, N.Y. and Suey Tang Pressing Laundry 30-78 31st St., Astoria, N.Y. into 1961 Asia Shirt Pressing Corp. 509 46th St., Brooklyn, N.Y. (worked a few months in 1961) Asia Shirt Pressing Corp. 509 46th St., Brooklyn, N.Y. and Quon Bing Tom (Restaurant) 157 Belmont Ave., Newark, N.J. (these two places in 1962) Asia Shirt Pressing Corp. 509 46th St., Brooklyn, N.Y. and Broadway Pressing Co. 5060 Broadway, New York, N.Y. (these two places in 1963 & 1964) Four K Laundry 9 Foxhurst Road, Baldwin, N.Y. -- in 1965 Bamboo Hut Lexington, Mass. beginning March 8, 1966 @$200.00 monthly. Work by the piece in shirt pressing laundries. No set weekly wages. Cannot remember the exact date of each beginning and ending.
